            <title>[SPARK-12056] NewHadoopRDD: TaskAttemptContext should be created only after calling setConf.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12056</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TaskAttemptContext&apos;s constructor will clone the configuration instead of referencing it. Calling setConf after creating TaskAttemptContext makes any changes to the configuration inside setConf unperceived by RecordReader instances.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
